20/04/2010
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Police detained more than 30 doctors and officials of the Pension and Disability Insurance Fund on Monday (April 19th) for suspected fraud. The investigation started a year ago. Among those arrested were doctors from state and private hospitals who allegedly diagnosed patients without disabilities to allow them to receive pensions. The patients are believed to have paid at least 1,500 euros for the fake documents. (A1, MIA, Makfax, Sitel, Alsat - 19/04/10)
